 class=m><span class=title> RE.</span><hr size=1> None of the above abilities are &quot;negated&quot; vs. Styles or crits.<br>
<br>
Evade, Block and Parry all work.. imo (sometimes) too well against styles and crits as you can lose an entire chain due to one single block, parry or evade.  Though that post does apply in the reverse. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=prudetristan>PrudeTristan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/5/02 12:59:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3072.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Reply</span><hr size=1> We as shadowblades have a 30 percent damage bonus in our favor vs inf and nightshades.  We get a 15 bonus to leather you get a 15 minus to leather.  See the problem.  You cant and wont ever kill a shadowblade in straight melee.  Stop trying you are not ment to kill us.<br>
<br>
Prude <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvalarauco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valarauco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/5/02 1:40:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3072.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~bdemong/valaface.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> DO NOT</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> want Detect Hidden to be any better than it is.  Anything that makes assassins easier for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> anyone</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to see makes it harder to be an assassin.<br>
<br>
Suggestion for balancing Nightshades against the other two: double the damage on our shout, halve the timer to 10 seconds, or both. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umenaandr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Menaan DR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/5/02 11:50:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3072.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> Zedie, I know you've supposed to turn this in by now and I can just pray you didn't submit that stuff about an outer detect radius.  And if you did I pray they throw it to the garbage.<br>
<br>
Even if they only send the message, they would still have to check to make sure you are an assassin with detect hidden before they could send it to you or else the people without detect hidden but with a cheat prog could have the ability to have this outer detect radius.  And you know what this causes when you put that code in on the server to check every person that comes into that outer detect radius on an assassin.. it causes more lag.  When you make a server / client based program you need to have as little checks on the server as possible.  Because you have to remember .. My computer has to send information all the way to the server, the other guys has to send it the server has to receive it all read it and figure out what to do with it then send it all the way back to both people.<br>
<br>
Another check like the one that would be required to implement what you speak of would had another few milliseconds to the delay of sending it back probably.  And IMO as a programmer myself on something that already can have a 1/2 sec delay, adding a few more milliseconds is unacceptable.<br>
<br>
Not to mention the fact that I dont want this skill.  If I get it that means other assassins are going to get it and that means whenever we are out hunting were going to be given away a lot sooner than we should.  You'll then see lots having a pet rogue following them around of really low level.. just high enough to have detect hidden and get this skill.  They see that go off and they know to get moving way before we have a chance to get in and strike. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umenaandr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Menaan DR</A> at: 5/5/02 11:50:23 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzedia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zedia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/5/02 5:16:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3072.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> While having a pet rogue follow you around is a concern that I also was thinking of this weekend I still don't agree that this would be any sort of compromise for cheaters or create lag.  The server knows what is going on.  It knows if you are an assassin and if you have detect hidden.  All the client does is feed the server movements and actions.  The server itself can decide if there is an enemy stealther near you and make all the checks before sending anything down the pipeline to you.  There would not be any lag added since it would all be server side except for the single message string it would send you.  Worst come to worst it would just require more hardware at Mythic's end. <p>Zedisa - Nightshade TL</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwoopya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Woopya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/5/02 6:52:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3072.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /reply</span><hr size=1> Some of my added concerns and replies to your ideas:<br>
<br>
1) evade, for which shades have the best follow up style, is NOT happening enough in RvR(diamondback.) I tend to think it is broken. I can see from some posts above many of you think it isnt broken. Broken or not, it isnt happening enough. The 2 stats evade works off of are the 2 stats which shades tend to be stocked in. Therefor, if evade worked better in RvR, the assassin class that needs it most would benefit most. Make shades evade more in RvR, like we do in PvE.<br>
<br>
2) HIgh quickness should NOT have a nagative effect on hidden strike dmg attacks. It does follow roleplay reasoning and it doesnt follow real reasoning. <br>
<br>
3)  lessening our argo from hidden attacks will not imrove our PvE groupability. We still wont offer anything any other class can do at least as well as us. Instead, i would like to see our spelline improved. This is what sets us apart from other assassins, and it is in much need of repair. Give us a spell that improves the chance of crit hits for all tanks/casters in our group. That is just 1 idea.<br>
<br>
4) Improve CD. It is the most imcomplete spec skill in the game(cave magic tied) It is no use to shades and improving it would also help BM's, another class nearly extinct.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=quaysh>Quaysh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/6/02 3:13:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3072.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reply</span><hr size=1> For making us more desirable in groups - I suggest making backstab positional only and not requiring us to be hidden. If they are worried about the fact that we would be able to do it more than once on a mob, well, they don't seem to have a problem with landing multiple nukes on a mob from casters, whats the difference? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=3072.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=3072.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3072.topic&index=23><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=3072.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=3072.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTo